# --- hive runtime (repo-local state that must not be committed) ---
# Ignore what is *inside* .hive/, not .hive/ itself: git cannot re-include a
# file whose parent directory is excluded, so a bare `.hive/` would make the
# negation below dead on arrival. The `/*` form keeps the directory walkable.
.hive/*
# The dev-only skills are committed by design (SPEC.md): they are instructions
# for working on Hive's own source, and packaging.test.ts scans them to prove
# none of them reach a user's binary. Ignored, they vanished from every clone
# and worktree and took that guard down with them.
!.hive/skills/
# .hive/memory/ stays out on purpose — this repo is public and the facts in it
# are internal. packaging.test.ts synthesizes a stand-in corpus when they are
# absent, which is everywhere but this machine.

#Coding Agents
.claude/
.codex/
# hive writes the grok MCP wiring here at spawn (see writeGrokAgentConfig), the
# same way it writes .mcp.json for claude. Nothing is tracked under .grok/, so
# the bare-directory form is safe here — unlike .hive/, which needed .hive/*
# because a bare rule would have deleted its committed skills from every clone.
.grok/
# hive writes per-worktree MCP wiring at spawn (see writeClaudeAgentConfig)
.mcp.json
# hive symlinks shared skills into each worktree at spawn (see
# src/adapters/skills.ts); not anchored to .hive/worktrees/ because this
# file is evaluated from each worktree's own root, where that path never
# matches.
.agents/

apple
